main event: A civilian observed a star-like object moving from west to east for about 5 minutes in Manhattan on 15 June 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed at an elevation of 70-75 degrees., The observer was a 39-year-old TV producer, who is described as probably reliable., The sighting took place at night and lasted for about 5 minutes., The object moved in a straight path from west to east before sinking below the skyline., The official conclusion of the report labeled the sighting as a satellite.
